"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paralympics-paris-alfie-hewett-gordon-reid-china-french-b2609130.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Lauren Rowles made rowing history, archer Jodie Grinham won gold while pregnant, and wheelchair tennis duoAlfie HewettandGordon Reidburied lingering trauma during 11 action-packed days inParis.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jodie_Grinham\", \"score\": 0.9999980121030353, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jodie Grinham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jodie_Grinham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jodie_Grinham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Javelin star Dan Pembroke, schoolgirls Bly Twomey and Iona Winnifrith, and Britain's men's wheelchair basketball team also hit the headlines at the first Paralympic Games to be staged in theFrenchcapital.\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javelin_throw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3954119138083413e-16, \"text\": \"Javelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javelin_throw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Javelin_throw\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pembroke_Parish\", \"score\": 0.9999997707928096, \"rank\": 2.2920509531373496e-07, \"text\": \"Pembroke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pembroke_Parish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pembroke_Parish\"}, {\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\", \"score\": 0.9999968999621008, \"rank\": 1.5750802757853745e-06, \"text\": \"Iona\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\"}, {\"begin\": 616, \"end\": 623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9998058969047516, \"rank\": 0.000194140777797213, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, the PA news agency picks out some of the standout moments.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rowles starred as Britain celebrated its greatest day of Paralympic rowing by grabbing three golds and a silver on a super Sunday at Vaires-sur-Marne Stadium.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 831, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9998058969047516, \"rank\": 0.000194140777797213, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 26-year-old became the sport's first female triple champion after powering pastChinain the PR2 mixed doubles alongside former Royal Engineer Commando Gregg Stevenson.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Engineers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Royal Engineer\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Engineers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Royal_Engineers\"}, {\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregg_Allman\", \"score\": 0.9999999773949642, \"rank\": 2.2604100912394513e-08, \"text\": \"Gregg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregg_Allman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregg_Allman\"}, {\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Louis_Stevenson\", \"score\": 0.9999995896838232, \"rank\": 4.0987307879112327e-07, \"text\": \"Stevenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Louis_Stevenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Louis_Stevenson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is definitely the best one yet,\\\" she said, after adding to her Rio and Tokyo triumphs with Laurence Whiteley.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5033352156730805e-14, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.360132607157442e-16, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1240, \"end\": 1257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurence_Whiteley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laurence Whiteley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurence_Whiteley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurence_Whiteley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What feels better than making history?\\\"\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pembroke made little secret of his desire to retain the F13 javelin title by breaking the world record.\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He more than delivered thanks to a gladiatorial-esque display at Stade de France.\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visually-impaired Pembroke whipped up the crowd before blowing kisses, bowing and performing an impromptu lap of honour wrapped in the Union Jack after initially stretching the previous best global mark and then smashing it with a mammoth throw of 74.49 metres.\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The crowd just got behind me and that was my secret weapon,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hewett and Reid suffered painful defeats to French pair Stephane Houdet and Nicolas Peifer in the gold medal matches at Rio 2016 and Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999142611537248, \"rank\": 8.477239156498429e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1877, \"end\": 1892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St\\u00e9phane_Houdet\", \"score\": 0.9999999784899958, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephane Houdet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St\\u00e9phane_Houdet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St\\u00e9phane_Houdet\"}, {\"begin\": 1897, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Peifer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Peifer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Peifer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Peifer\"}, {\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.360132607157442e-16, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pair completed a career golden slam by finally ending their wait for Paralympic doubles glory.\", \"from\": 1966, \"to\": 2064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's the stuff of dreams,\\\" said Hewett, following a dominant 6-2 6-1 win over Takuya Miki and Tokito Oda at Roland Garros.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hewett fell agonisingly short against Oda in the singles final 24 hours later in one of the greatest matches in wheelchair tennis history.\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grinham spent time at a Paris maternity ward thinking she may be going into early labour, before winning two medals.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2353, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0874618139865948e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At seven months pregnant, she dramatically snatched bronze from defending champion Phoebe Paterson Pine in the individual compound event.\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoebe_Paterson_Pine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phoebe Paterson Pine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoebe_Paterson_Pine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoebe_Paterson_Pine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three days later, the 31-year-old surpassed that feat by winning gold with Nathan Macqueen in the mixed team compound.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2659, \"end\": 2674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_MacQueen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathan Macqueen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_MacQueen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_MacQueen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked how she will relay the tales to her unborn child, Grinham said: \\\"It will be like, 'You were on the podium - the youngest member to be on the podium'.\\\"\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amy Truesdale and Matt Bush wrote their names into the history books by grabbing Great Britain's maiden Paralympic taekwondo golds.\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2861, \"end\": 2874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Truesdale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Amy Truesdale\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Truesdale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amy_Truesdale\"}, {\"begin\": 2879, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bush_(baseball)\", \"score\": 0.6522727071482854, \"rank\": 0.5330996884735328, \"text\": \"Matt Bush\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bush_(baseball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Bush_(baseball)\"}, {\"begin\": 2942, \"end\": 2955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999955791242833, \"rank\": 4.380554154388154e-06, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Truesdale jubilantly celebrated with a one-handed handstand and by performing the splits in the centre of the octagon following victory over Guljonoy Naimova in the women's K44 +65kg final.\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sometimes you think, 'Is it worth it?'.\", \"from\": 3183, \"to\": 3223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, it's definitely worth it,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Closing ceremony flagbearer Bush backed up the landmark success by beating Russian Aliaskhab Ramazanov in the men's K44 +80kg event.\", \"from\": 3268, \"to\": 3400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3296, \"end\": 3300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\", \"score\": 0.999898670066286, \"rank\": 0.00010124917366830262, \"text\": \"Bush\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_W._Bush\"}, {\"begin\": 3343, \"end\": 3350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9964150800692135, \"rank\": 0.0035970039942753865, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain's quest for an historic first Paralympic wheelchair basketball gold was scuppered as the United States completed a 'three-peat' in the men's final.\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3402, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999955791242833, \"rank\": 4.380554154388154e-06, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3505, \"end\": 3518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.963432483249758, \"rank\": 0.03790402462568157, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A crowd of 20,000 crammed into Bercy Arena on the last evening of competition.\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3595, \"end\": 3606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following bronzes in 2004, 2008, 2016 and 2021, GB moved within three points of the back-to-back defending champions with just under 12 seconds remaining.\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3691, \"end\": 3693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999798858383865, \"rank\": 2.0114566205590057e-05, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But they could not complete a sensational comeback.\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver represented their best result since losing the 1996 final to Australia.\", \"from\": 3850, \"to\": 3928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3918, \"end\": 3927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999880224096, \"rank\": 1.1722916412699242e-08, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At just 27, the combined age of Twomey and Winnifrith is precisely half that of GB's oldest Paris Paralympian Jeanette Chippington.\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 4061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4010, \"end\": 4012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9999798858383865, \"rank\": 2.0114566205590057e-05, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4022, \"end\": 4027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0874618139865948e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4040, \"end\": 4060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanette_Chippington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeanette Chippington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanette_Chippington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeanette_Chippington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Twomey, 14, became Britain's youngest table tennis medallist with doubles bronze alongside Fliss Pickard, before replicating the achievement in singles.\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4081, \"end\": 4088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9998058969047516, \"rank\": 0.000194140777797213, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hours after the second of Twomey's bronzes, swimmer Winnifrith emulated her idol Ellie Simmonds by standing on the podium aged 13.\", \"from\": 4215, \"to\": 4345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4296, \"end\": 4310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Simmonds\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ellie Simmonds\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Simmonds\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellie_Simmonds\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She posted a lifetime best to claim 100m breaststroke silver.\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Away from British achievements, a milestone moment arrived on the opening day of the Games when Zakia Khudadadi clinched a maiden medal for the Refugee Paralympic Team.\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4419, \"end\": 4426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.999185560725325, \"rank\": 0.0007463842634122299, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4505, \"end\": 4520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakia_Khudadadi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zakia Khudadadi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakia_Khudadadi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zakia_Khudadadi\"}, {\"begin\": 4553, \"end\": 4576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Paralympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Paralympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Paralympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Paralympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Paralympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taekwondo star Khudadadi, from Afghanistan, claimed bronze in the women's K44 -47kg category.\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4578, \"end\": 4587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_Taekwondo\", \"score\": 0.9997197457334912, \"rank\": 0.0002803328308132265, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Para_Taekwondo\"}, {\"begin\": 4609, \"end\": 4620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9945978156671895, \"rank\": 0.005430270952280093, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Paralympic Committee president Andrew Parsons singled out the achievement as a personal highlight.\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4672, \"end\": 4706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Paralympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4717, \"end\": 4731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Parsons_(sports_administrator)\", \"score\": 0.8546160279867977, \"rank\": 0.13434022257553296, \"text\": \"Andrew Parsons\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Parsons_(sports_administrator)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Parsons_(sports_administrator)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Visually-impaired Cameroonian runner Guillaume Junior Atangana, who lives in West Yorkshire, later added a second medal for the team by completing the podium in the men's T11 400m.\", \"from\": 4785, \"to\": 4965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4839, \"end\": 4847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdon_Atangana\", \"score\": 0.9999953196006964, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atangana\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdon_Atangana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdon_Atangana\"}, {\"begin\": 4862, \"end\": 4876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res